  <li>Fraser Davidson</li>
</ul>

<p>Smalltalk Blue Book</p>
<ul>
  <li>implementation of Smalltalk in a subset of Smalltalk</li>
  <li>beautiful simplicity</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.mirandabanda.org/bluebook/">http://www.mirandabanda.org/bluebook/</a></li>
</ul>

<p>SmallC</p>
<ul>
  <li>very straight-forward implementation of a C compiler that could (IMO) be ported to any modern language</li>
  <li>https://ia801008.us.archive.org/19/items/dr_dobbs_journal_vol_05_201803/dr_dobbs_journal_vol_05.pdf](https://ia801008.us.archive.org/19/items/dr_dobbs_journal_vol_05_201803/dr_dobbs_journal_vol_05.pdf)</li>
  <li>(see Dr. Dobb’s Journal number 45, May 1980 “A Small C Compiler for the 8080’s)</li>
  <li>beautiful simplicity, easy to understand compiler</li>
  <li>Ron Cain</li>
</ul>

<p>Anatomy of Lisp</p>
<ul>
  <li>a Lisp Compiler written in a functional style</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.ca/Anatomy-Lisp-John-Allen/dp/007001115X">https://www.amazon.ca/Anatomy-Lisp-John-Allen/dp/007001115X</a></li>
